status_message:
Happy Holidays from the AthenaHacks team and Aubrie the owl <3 
Enjoy your winter break and don't forget to sign up for updates for Southern California's premier all-female hackathon at http://athenahacks.com/!
Hey friends! While you're waiting for the AthenaHacks application, check out SBHacks - another great opportunity for learning and building! <3
Happy thanksgiving everyone!! We're grateful for all of your support for women in tech and we can't wait to see you at AthenaHacks! Check out our new website if you haven't yet at AthenaHacks.com :)
Check out our new look and website! http://AthenaHacks.com

TL;DR: If you're interested in supporting women in tech, come to AthenaHacks!

From February 11-12 at USC, join AthenaHacks for a weekend of building and learning in an open and supportive environment. AthenaHacks is a hackathon for high school and college women of any major and background in Los Angeles! If you're interested in attending, go to AthenaHacks.com to find out why AthenaHacks is fantastically different and drop us your email so you can be updated when applications and more information comes out! Email us at AthenaHacks@gmail.com if you have more questions! Code on <3

Hey all! AthenaHacks is looking for CAMPUS AMBASSADORS at various schools in Southern California (especially the smaller ones) to help us get the word out. If you're interested in helping out the cause (go women in tech!!, go hackathons!!) pls message us or comment below :)
Happy Halloween! :)
HEY FRIENDS! Guess what? We've got an official date and location for you!! Mark your calendars for February 11-12 at the University of Southern California's ballroom ❤️ We're excited to have you!

Helloooooo! We're super excited about all the enthusiasm we've received from people applying to be a part of Project Athena! We're wrapping up the application process soon (September 30) so now's the time to apply if you're interested! http://goo.gl/QhteCE

Athena Hacks needs DESIGNERS and WEB DEVELOPERS! If you're interested in helping with design/our website, please message us or email us at athenahacks@gmail.com. A great opportunity for you to have fun designin' and being creative while helping to bring more women into tech!

Interested in joining the Project Athena team? Apply here: http://goo.gl/QhteCE

Check out the list of the committees that will make up Project Athena to see which one you'd be interested in joining: http://goo.gl/bjORKU
